Text: (At last...he's here.)
(The formidable foe who defeated Delta...)

(Just as the Numbers reported, his weapons of choice
are wires...)

When the freight train reaches her, Alpha leaps onto
it.
Hello, John Smith.
And—good-bye.
However, John Smith blocks Alpha's surprise attack.
You hide your real, thinner wires in among decoys.
Right there...!

Dodged it, huh? Well, guess I should've expected as
much.
Ack!

In the darkness, countless wires controlled by John
Smith assail Alpha.

Alpha watches the wires, slices them away with her
sword, then goes in for a counterattack in the space
between their strikes.
It's fast and nimble—the perfect slash.

Alpha questions why his skills far surpass her
expectations.
His movements...
His timing...
His precise techniques...
*gasp*

Alpha takes a wide berth and steps back from the
battle altogether.
This...can't be...
No...! Why?!
Why is it you?!
Alpha is certain about it.
Shadow!
I've abandoned that name.
I'm John Smith now.
But why are you John Smith?
Because it was the best option.

The best option for what? That isn't enough to
understand what's going on.
Delta—
What about Delta?!
...Delta's off on a long journey.
*gasp*
That...!
That doesn't tell me anything!!!

I'm dumb, so I don't understand all the things you
do. I'm weak, so I can't do all the things you can.
But still, even so...
I want to understand, so I can support you!

You saved me, so I want to do whatever it is
I can to help!

But you're always going forward on your own, leaving
me just gazing at your back...
Do you not need me anymore?
...You'll know once this is all over.
This was the best option—
//ムービー再生
Wait—
Agh...ahh...!
Wait...
Her voice doesn't reach him.
Don't leave me...
The train moves on, leaving Alpha behind.
The day has finally come.
They are swimming in millions of gold coins.
What do you think, John?
...Simply amazing.

Most of the counterfeit bills have been redeemed.
The MCA's vaults must be totally empty now.

Now all we have to do is publicly redeem the real
bills we've been collecting, and it's all over for
them.

The only concern is whether the townspeople will keep
the bills... The people will be scrambling to redeem
their bills first, and the MCA will collapse due to a
lack of funds.
Before long, this will ripple down to Mitsugoshi too.

Not even Mitsugoshi can exchange all of the bills in
the market.

The large companies that sustain the kingdom's
economy will all start to collapse, and the nation
will be pushed to its limits trying to control the
resultant chaos.

That'll be our opportunity to destroy all the evidence
and make ourselves scarce.

That's right... As the amount of counterfeit bills in
circulation increases, prices will also rise.

The situation is leading to inflation, and it's
becoming a major factor for the kingdom
that cannot be ignored.
...It's the perfect time to finish it.

...Your foresight is as good as ever. This plan
wouldn't have been a success without you, John.
Hmph...I can't take all the credit.
How kind of you to say.

I talked about it before—about the time I lived with
my mother when I was young—

And about how I was fourteen, and Gettan was
seventeen...
